  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And in each of the outlying kibbutzim-- and Amir was very outlying, it was in the upper [?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Galilee-- ?] there was a small group, small cadre, of Palmahniks, Palmah, people of the Palmah.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And we went [? through ?] a very [? rigorous ?] training.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was an [INAUDIBLE] training, because the British forces didn't allow Jews to have, legally, any weapons.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Every weapon had to be obtained illegally, sometimes under very difficult and costly circumstances.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And when we trained, we had to train by night and out of the sight of Arab eyes.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And, you know, it was not an-- an open training.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But we were very well trained.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And sometimes we were called to action.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And one action I have in-- in mind to-- to bring to your remembrance, one night, seven bridges were destroyed in-- in Palestine as an protest against the British taking Jewish people to the prison camp in Athlit.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And when the Jordan bridge was exploded in the vicinity of Jerusalem, I was there, and I played a part [? about ?] it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "At the time, we were called terrorists.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] It changes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We were very active when the illegal immigration of refugees from Europe started, because the British never allowed the surviving Jews from the-- the survivors of the concentration camps from Germany and Austria coming to Italy and looking for the way to come to Palestine to come to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "A matter of fact, every one ship they caught they sent either to Cyprus or to [?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Mauritius-- ?] to islands.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But they never let them land.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But many boats were able to bring survivors in.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "They were taken in by the Palmah, dispersed in the kibbutzim, and they just disappeared in the country.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
